    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There is a lot of talk about relaxation in the horse world. But I believe that the word is misleading as it conjures up images of lying around on a sofa or in bed. It goes without saying that we don’t want tension. We want that middle point where things are at their natural length but no more than that. Take an elastic band and just hold it at each side. That is total relaxation. Now pull the two ends until the band is tight. This is tension. Now move your fingers until the band is just straight. There is no tension – but no total relaxation either. ",
      "id": "1818681141732"
    },
